TY  - JOUR
T1  - Retrospective Reports In Organizational Research: A Reexamination Of Recent Evidence
AU  - Miller, C. Chet
AU  - Cardinal, Laura B.
AU  - Glick, William H.
Y1  - 1997/02/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/257026
DO  - 10.5465/257026
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 189
EP  - 204
VL  - 40
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Retrospective reports of important organizational phenomena are commonly fused in strategic management and organization theory research. A recent study, however, suggested that these reports tend to be inaccurate and seriously questioned their use. Our reexamination of this study suggests the situation is not so dire. Our work suggests that retrospective reporting is a viable research methodology if the measure used to generate the reports is adequately reliable and valid. Retrospective reports should neither be rejected nor used indiscriminately.
AB  - Retrospective reports of important organizational phenomena are commonly fused in strategic management and organization theory research. A recent study, however, suggested that these reports tend to be inaccurate and seriously questioned their use. Our reexamination of this study suggests the situation is not so dire. Our work suggests that retrospective reporting is a viable research methodology if the measure used to generate the reports is adequately reliable and valid. Retrospective reports should neither be rejected nor used indiscriminately.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/257026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/257026
Y2  - 2026/04/24
