T1  - Effect Of Race On Promotions To Top Management In A Federal Department
AU  - Powell, Gary N.
AU  - Butterfield, D. Anthony
Y1  - 1997/02/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/257022
DO  - 10.5465/257022
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 112
EP  - 128
VL  - 40
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Applicant race did not directly affect promotion decisions for top management positions in a cabinet-level U.S. government department with standardized promotion practices that include a panel review process. However, race indirectly affected promotion decisions through key job-relevant variables, to the disadvantage of applicants of color.
AB  - Applicant race did not directly affect promotion decisions for top management positions in a cabinet-level U.S. government department with standardized promotion practices that include a panel review process. However, race indirectly affected promotion decisions through key job-relevant variables, to the disadvantage of applicants of color.
