TY  - JOUR
T1  - Technical and Strategic Human Resources Management Effectiveness as Determinants of Firm Performance
AU  - Huselid, Mark A.
AU  - Jackson, Susan E.
AU  - Schuler, Randall S.
Y1  - 1997/02/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/257025
DO  - 10.5465/257025
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 171
EP  - 188
VL  - 40
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We evaluated the impact of human resource (HR) managers' capabilities on HR management effectiveness and the latter's impact on corporate financial performance. For 293 U.S. firms, effectiveness was associated with capabilities and attributes of HR staff. We also found relationships between HR management effectiveness and productivity, cash flow, and market value. Findings were consistent across market and accounting measures of performance and with corrections for biases.
AB  - We evaluated the impact of human resource (HR) managers' capabilities on HR management effectiveness and the latter's impact on corporate financial performance. For 293 U.S. firms, effectiveness was associated with capabilities and attributes of HR staff. We also found relationships between HR management effectiveness and productivity, cash flow, and market value. Findings were consistent across market and accounting measures of performance and with corrections for biases.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/257025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/257025
Y2  - 2026/04/24
